text: Laimonas Chatkevičius (born January 7, 1993) is a professional Lithuanian basketball player who last played for Neptūnas Klaipėda of the Lithuanian Basketball League. He plays at the Center position.https://www.basketnews.lt/zaidejai/6559-laimonas-chatkevicius.html == Professional career == After graduating from the South Carolina Gamecocks,https://www.basketnews.lt/news-96132-laimonas-chatkevicius-ir- mindaugas-kacinas-baige-karjera-ncaa.html Chatkevičius signed a one-year deal with MKS Dąbrowa Górnicza.https://www.basketnews.lt/news-104548-jegas-nba- vasaros-lygoje-ismegines-laimonas-chatkevicius-rungtyniaus-lenkijoje.html On 2017-18 season he signed with AZS Koszalin, but in February Chatkevičius come back to Lithuania, and signed with Neptūnas Klaipėda for the rest of the season. == International career == Chatkevičius played in 2013 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship for Lithuania men's national under-20, averaging 7,9 points, 8,1 rebounds per game. == References == Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Lithuanian men's basketball players Category:Lithuanian expatriate basketball people in the United States Category:BC Neptūnas players Category:Power forwards (basketball) Category:South Carolina Gamecocks men's basketball players Category:Sportspeople from Klaipėda
